FBIS4-30817 "dreeu104_y_94006" FBIS-EEU-94-104 Daily Report 31 May 1994 YUGOSLAVIA Serbia Churkin Comments Churkin Comments LD3105115594 Belgrade TANJUG in English 1130 GMT 31 May 94 LD3105115594 Belgrade TANJUG English BFN [Text] Belgrade, May 31 (TANJUG) -- Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic on Tuesday conferred with Russian presidential envoy Vitaliy Churkin about the latest aspects of settling the Bosnian conflict and about the republic of Serb Krajina-Croatia relations. In a brief statement to the press, Churkin said that the first step in resolving the Bosnian conflict was an overall cessation of hostilities, which, he stressed, enjoyed strong Belgrade's support.
